The owner has the ability to create any subnodes of its choosing, however only the DeveloperRegistry is able to change both the owner and the resolver for a given node once created. The ChipRegistry is able to change the owner of a node (signifying a transfer of a chip) but is not able to  change the resolver. These permissions are put in place in order to maintain a track record of authenticity for chips while allowing the DeveloperRegistry to re-assign sub-domains to new DeveloperRegistrars.
